Description: Up for sale, a rare Kramer "Proaxe" guitar circa 1989-1990. These seem to be in short supply out there. This guitar looks pretty good but it does have some issues. Cosmetics and physical condition are excellent, nothing bad to report here. Neck is straight and frets look good. The finish is gloss black. Issues: I believe the neck pickup and middle pickup are NOT ORIGINAL, the ones I've seen online have hot-rails type pickups. In addition, there is something funky going on with the wiring here (likely related to the above). The selector switch appears to NOT do anything in position 1,2,3 (4 and 5 are active and produce sound). The other switch on the body appears to be an on/off for output. (I don't know if that is correct or not.) Also of note: I do not see a serial number on the neck plate (it doesn't look like it has been messed with but I would have expected the serial number to be here). Sold under the trending price (I'm seeing $1600-1700 for similar) to account for some work that this will need before being "correct". Includes new style gator hard case which is in good condition. US bidders/buyers only please. This item will ship tracked and insured.
Title: Rare Vintage Kramer Proaxe Deluxe Guitar - Circa 1989-1990 - Black
